          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The photodisintegration  of  Li-6  by  bremsstrahlung",
                " radiation   of   17.3-MeV   end-point   energy   was",
                " investigated by use  of  coincidence  techniques  to",
                " detect    neutron-proton    coincidences    and   by",
                " measurement of the photoproton energy  spectra.  The",
                " Li-6(gamma,n)  reaction  is  found to Be responsible",
                " for 0.58(0.13) of the photoneutron yield measured by",
                " Romanowski    while   the   Li-6(g,p)He-5   reaction",
                " contributes 0.31(0.04) of the  yield.  No  angularly",
                " correlated neutron-proton coincidences were detected",
                " which would support a deuteron-alpha-particle  model",
                " for   the   Li-6(g,np)He-4   reaction;   however,the",
                " possible  existence  of   this   reaction   is   not",
                " eliminated."
              ]
            }
          ],
